Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprText: CASE WHEN "%1" < 18 THEN 'A: <18' WHEN "%1" < 25 THEN 'B: 18-25' WHEN "%1" < 35 THEN 'C: 25-35' WHEN "%1" < 45 THEN 'D: 35-45' WHEN "%1" < 55 THEN 'E: 45-55' WHEN "%1" < 65 THEN 'F: 55-65' WHEN "%1" IS NULL THEN 'Unspecified' ELSE 'G: >65' END
Expr.ExprTextDesc: CASE WHEN "Marketing Contact List"."Dim - Contact"."Age" < 18 THEN 'A: <18' WHEN "Marketing Contact List"."Dim - Contact"."Age" < 25 THEN 'B: 18-25' WHEN "Marketing Contact List"."Dim - Contact"."Age" < 35 THEN 'C: 25-35' WHEN "Marketing Contact List"."Dim - Contact"."Age" < 45 THEN 'D: 35-45' WHEN "Marketing Contact List"."Dim - Contact"."Age" < 55 THEN 'E: 45-55' WHEN "Marketing Contact List"."Dim - Contact"."Age" < 65 THEN 'F: 55-65' WHEN "Marketing Contact List"."Dim - Contact"."Age" IS NULL THEN 'Unspecified' ELSE 'G: >65' END

LogicalColumn.name: Mosaic Group
LogicalColumn.Description: Mosaic Group refers to 15 main socio-economic groups in which UK population has been categorized by Mosaic UK, which is Experian's people classification system. CRUK uses 'Mosaic Public Sector 2009'.

LogicalColumn.name: Gift Aid Amount
LogicalColumn.Description: This OBI Field is no longer in use, please refer to the Gift Aid Reporting Guidelines for alternatives (available from Data.Help)

LogicalColumn.name: 4 Year Income
LogicalColumn.Description: 6 Year Income: Payments made in the last 6 years, starting from April 6.For Instance to calculate from 'July 10 2009', the income value (Cash and CoG) will be added from April 6,2003. After April '6 2010' this metric will comprise of values from 'April 6 2004'

LogicalColumn.name: Race Id
LogicalColumn.Description: Race Id given by RAPP to the supporters who have participated in Race for Life Events.

LogicalColumn.name: Postal Area
LogicalColumn.Description: The first one or two letters of the postcode (anything before the first number). For instance, if the postcode is PL14 4TE, the Postal Area is 'PL'

LogicalColumn.name: Postal District
LogicalColumn.Description: The first section of the postcode, before the last 3 characters. For instance, if the postcode is PL14 4TE, the Postal District is PL14

LogicalColumn.name: Postal Sector
LogicalColumn.Description: The postcode minus the last two letters. For instance, if the postcode is PL14 4TE, the Postal Sector is PL14 4

LogicalColumn.name: Household Flag
LogicalColumn.Description: This flag is Y if a supporter is part of a household.

LogicalColumn.name: Employee Flag
LogicalColumn.Description: Y for CRUK Employees, N otherwise.

LogicalColumn.name: Key Volunteer Flag
LogicalColumn.Description: Y for Key Volunteers, N otherwise.

LogicalColumn.name: Primary Canvasser
LogicalColumn.Description: The name of the employee who is currently canvassing this supporter and is ticked as ‘Primary’ in Siebel

LogicalColumn.name: Primary Canvasser Login
LogicalColumn.Description: The login of the employee who is currently canvassing this supporter and is ticked as ‘Primary’ in Siebel

LogicalColumn.name: Primary Canvasser Team
LogicalColumn.Description: The team to which the Primary Canvasser currently belongs

LogicalColumn.name: VF Region
LogicalColumn.Description: The CRUK region which the postal district belongs to as defined in the Postcode Admin table on Siebel e.g. PL14 is in Region 9

LogicalColumn.name: VF Regional Canvasser
LogicalColumn.Description: The Canvasser who is responsible for the area in which the supporter's primary address sits, as defined in the Postcode Admin table on Siebel

LogicalColumn.name: Legacy Region
LogicalColumn.Description: The Legacy Region which the postal district belongs to as defined in the Postcode Admin table on Siebel

LogicalColumn.name: Legacy Regional Canvasser
LogicalColumn.Description: The Regional Legacy Manager who is responsible for the region in which the supporter's primary address sits, as defined in the Postcode Admin table on Siebel

LogicalColumn.name: FWS Scheme Name
LogicalColumn.Description: The name of the Free Will Service scheme that covers the region in which the supporter's primary address sits, as defined in the Postcode Admin table on Siebel

LogicalColumn.name: Opportunity Confirmed Date
LogicalColumn.Description: The date that the Opportunity reached the 'Confirmed' stage

LogicalColumn.name: Reconfirmed Date
LogicalColumn.Description: The date that the commitment was last confirmed. For Legacies, this is when the pledge was last confirmed to be in place

LogicalColumn.name: Reconfirmed Source
LogicalColumn.Description: The source of the reconfirmation of the commitment. For Legacies, this is the source that led to the pledge being confirmed

LogicalColumn.name: Reconfirmed Source Description
LogicalColumn.Description: The source of the reconfirmation of the commitment. For Legacies, this is the source that led to the pledge being confirmed

LogicalColumn.name: Pledge Type
LogicalColumn.Description: The pledge product. Where there are multiple pledge products on the opportunity, this will be 'Multiple'

LogicalColumn.name: Percentage
LogicalColumn.Description: For Legacies, this is the percentage of the owning party's estate that they have stipulated must be left to CRUK in their will.

LogicalColumn.name: Estimated Amount
LogicalColumn.Description: Estimated pledge amount

LogicalColumn.name: Agreed Amount
LogicalColumn.Description: Known pledge amount

LogicalColumn.name: # FWS Uses
LogicalColumn.Description: Number of times the Free Will Service has been used

LogicalColumn.name: First Opportunity Number
LogicalColumn.Description: The Opportunity Number of the supporter's earliest Opportunity with a Journey of 'Free Will Service'

LogicalColumn.name: First Will Type
LogicalColumn.Description: Will Type from the supporter's first opportunity

LogicalColumn.name: First Will Date
LogicalColumn.Description: Will Date from the supporter's first opportunity

LogicalColumn.name: First Estimated Amount
LogicalColumn.Description: Total Estimated Amount from the supporter's first opportunity

LogicalColumn.name: First Agreed Amount
LogicalColumn.Description: Total Agreed Amount from the supporter's first opportunity

LogicalColumn.name: Last Opportunity Number
LogicalColumn.Description: The Opportunity Number of the supporter's most recent Opportunity with a Journey of 'Free Will Service'

LogicalColumn.name: Last Will Type
LogicalColumn.Description: Will Type from the supporter's latest opportunity

LogicalColumn.name: Last Will Date
LogicalColumn.Description: Will Date from the supporter's latest opportunity

LogicalColumn.name: Last Estimated Amount
LogicalColumn.Description: Total Estimated Amount from the supporter's latest opportunity

LogicalColumn.name: Last Agreed Amount
LogicalColumn.Description: Total Agreed Amount from the supporter's latest opportunity

LogicalColumn.name: First Opportunity Confirmed Date
LogicalColumn.Description: The date that the First Opportunity reached the 'Confirmed' stage

LogicalColumn.name: Last Opportunity Confirmed Date
LogicalColumn.Description: The date that the Last Opportunity reached the 'Confirmed' stage
